<P>
   &UR; AVOIDING BURNS, BITES AND OTHER SUMMER HAZARDS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By RAQUEL E. PELZEL
 &UR; From Consumers Digest magazine &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Summer pleasures can easily turn into summer pain for the
unwary. Pelzel discusses how to avoid and treat the many
afflictions of summer, including skin cancer, eye damage from the
sun, dehydration, poison ivy and other allergic reactions, stings
and bites. (slugged: BC-PERILS-OF-SUMMER-(SUMMER)-NYTSF, priority
code r, category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FIRST JUVENILE BASEBALL LEAGUE HELPS BREAK DOWN CLASS BARRIERS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; 900 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By PETER F. STEVENS &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Juvenile baseball leagues such as Little League can be traced
back to 1908 in rural Waynesburg, Pa., where a group of
civic-minded citizens had the inspiration of organizing an
unstructured series of baseball games into a league. The league
represented democracy in action, as sons of factory workers played
side by side with sons of the affluent. (slugged:
BC-FIRST-JUVENILE-BASEBALL-LEAGUE-(SUMMER)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; REAL MEN DON'T PACK FOR THEMSELVES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,200 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By JIM SHAHIN &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From American Way magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   As a travel writer, Shahin would like to provide summer
vacationers with sage advice on how to pack. But the truth is,
Shahin confesses, he doesn't have any tips. In fact, he doesn't
pack his bags. His wife does. This arrangement, he believes, is
quite common: Women pack the suitcases, men take pride in
methodically fitting them in the car trunk. (slugged:
BC-REAL-MEN-DON'T-PACK-(SUMMER)-NYTSF, priority code r, category
code l) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TOUCHY ISSUES AT FAMILY REUNIONS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,200 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By JENNIFER CRICHTON &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From ``Family Reunion'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   While family reunions offer a unique opportunity to reconnect
with one's kin, they also can bring to the fore all the simmering
tensions in a family. Do you invite the black sheep? Should you
finally unveil the big family secret? Crichton addresses these
issues, and offers a hilarious bonus in collaboration with Miss
Manners: The Ten Commandments of Reunion Etiquette. (slugged:
BC-MISS-MANNERS-ON-REUNIONS-(SUMMER)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l) &QL;
