</P>
<P>
   Not many things make John Glenn squirm. Nerves of steel are part
of the legend, part of the hero package. After all, he's a fighter
pilot who flew 149 combat missions In World War II and Korea and
collected a host of medals in the process. This after losing a
friend to anti-aircraft fire in combat mission number one.
</P>
<P>
   Glenn has met with world leaders, and even made a hearty but
failed attempt to become one, losing his 1984 bid for president. He
was in California with Bobby Kennedy the night he was killed, and
flew to Boston in the morning to tell the Kennedy children.
</P>
<P>
   He's faced difficult things, and that's not to say things don't
effect him, but he handles them. Whatever it is, he deals.
