will probably land him in the major leagues someday soon. Then
there's Scott Makarewicz, a 31 year- old journeyman, who has played
on nine different teams and is savoring what could be his last
chance to make it to the big leagues. A look at the essence of
minor league baseball in Central Texas: a nightly carnival complete
with corny between inning antics, and fans like Mary Havard who
makes sure the nomadic players have pots, pans, and bedsheets while
on their journey to The Show. (Davenport, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
