</P>
<P>
   GOODWILL-GAMES _ NEW YORK _ The Goodwill Games were born in
1986, after back-to-back Olympic boycotts, as Ted Turner's
extravagant way of getting the super powers back on the same
playing field. The Goodwill Games, however, have survived, or
perhaps refused to go away. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED. EMBARGOED UNTIL SUNDAY 7/19.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-BASEBALL_ There is Lance Berkman, the 22- year-old first
round draft pick, whose uncanny ability to hit a baseball 400 feet
will probably land him in the major leagues someday soon. Then
there's Scott Makarewicz, a 31 year- old journeyman, who has played
on nine different teams and is savoring what could be his last
chance to make it to the big leagues. A look at the essence of
minor league baseball in Central Texas: a nightly carnival complete
with corny between inning antics, and fans like Mary Havard who
makes sure the nomadic players have pots, pans, and bedsheets while
on their journey to The Show. (Davenport, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL-BAR _ A primer on how the minor leagues work, and how
Double-A level, the level that should be coming to Austin, fits
into the entire scheme.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL-BOX _ Info box on the Generals and their history.
(Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   COWBOYS _ Fullback Daryl Johnston is making a comeback from his
neck surgery of last year. A talk with him about that. (Cantu,
Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   COWNOTE _ Notes and quotes from the Dallas Cowboys training
camp. (Cantu, Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   MILLER _ SAN ANTONIO, Texas _ Jay Miller, the general manager of
the Houston Astros' Triple- A affiliate in New Orleans, will assume
the same position with the minor-league baseball team Nolan Ryan
wants to move to Round Rock, Reid Ryan said recently. Starting at
the end of this season, Miller, 39, will become the GM of the
Jackson Generals, the Astros' Double-A affiliate, which is expected
to move to Round Rock for the 2000 season. (Davenport, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SWTEXAS-DIRECTOR _ Mike Alden isn't certain he would be the
University of Missouri's new athletic director if not for DeLoss
Dodds. Alden, the Southwest Texas State athletic director who was
introduced as the Tigers' AD, said he thinks Dodds, the University
of Texas athletic director, played a pivotal but discreet role in
his landing the job. Dodds is close friends with Chuck Neinas, who
served as a head-hunter to Missouri in its search for the successor
to Joe Castiglione, who resigned in April to become AD at Oklahoma.
(Riggs, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCGUIRE-SOUVENIR _ Like thousands of other kids, 12-year-old
Nathan Adams of Oakwood arrived at Busch Stadium in St. Louis last
Sunday, July 12, hoping for a souvenir. He left with the ball that
became Mark McGwire's 39th home run. (McClelland, Dayton Daily
News) MOVED.
</P>
